I'm sticking with my reason in post 87

@CES: The addition of a town-affiliated BP does not appreciably improve town odds. Furthermore, it is pro forma to have a scum-affiliated BP when there is a vig. From what I've seen, town-affiliated BP are comparatively rare, especially with a town vig. I think there is a far greater chance that there is a cop who is claiming VT (because it is a Catch-22 -- claim cop and the game may continue, but cop will be targeted for NK or role-block tonight; claim VT and the game will probably end in draw); than the chances are that Korts is a town-affiliated BP.<br>
<br>
@Korts: Unless scum confesses, the game will end today anyway -- the only question is whether it ends in draw or town loss.

I told you idiots that Korts was scum. How many times did someone say that he was CONFIRMED town? How confirmed is he now?<br>
<br>
@CES: Why did you put me at L-1 so quickly on LYLO? As I'm reading down from the top of the page, I figured for sure you were scum because townies just don't do that. Poor play on your part -- Korts didn't even have to argue to convince you.
